---
import SiteLayout from "../../../../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import Breadcrumbs from "../../../../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="What Happens After You Submit a Report to PoliceConduct.org"
  description="A draft overview of what contributors can expect after they submit a report to PoliceConduct.org, from intake and review through publication, follow-up, and corrections."
  pagePath="/news/2026/03/22/what-happens-after-you-submit-a-report-to-policeconduct-org/"
>
  <main class="">
    <section class="py-vh-3 bg-gray-100 border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <Breadcrumbs
          items={[
            { label: "News", href: "/news/" },
            {
              label: "After You Submit a Report",
              href: "/news/2026/03/22/what-happens-after-you-submit-a-report-to-policeconduct-org/",
              current: true,
            },
          ]}
        />
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-10">
            <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-2">Coming Soon</p>
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">
              What Happens After You Submit a Report to PoliceConduct.org
            </h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted mb-0">
              <strong>Dover, Delaware — March 22, 2026</strong> — PoliceConduct.org
              is preparing a public guide that explains what happens after a report
              is submitted, including intake, review, follow-up, publication, and
              corrections.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <p>
          Many people hesitate to submit a police conduct report because they do
          not know what happens next. This upcoming article will explain the
          review path in plain language so contributors understand what the team
          checks, why some submissions take longer than others, and how updates
          or corrections can be added later.
        </p>
        <p>
          The goal is simple: reduce uncertainty for contributors and make the
          publication process easier to trust.
        </p>

        <h2 class="h4 text-uppercase text-muted mt-5">Planned Topics</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>How submissions enter the review queue</li>
          <li>What details help a report move faster</li>
          <li>Why the team may ask for clarification or supporting material</li>
          <li>How publication decisions are made</li>
          <li>
            How contributors can check status and submit corrections later
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
